<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-08-31T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-08-31T16:00:00-05:00" n="549" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d549">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/9815: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Grew</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-08-31T17:00:00-04:00">August 31, 1937—5
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>184. Your 329, August 31, 2 p.m. In the light of the contents of telegram
                            under reference and of your 322, August 27, 7 p.m., it seems to
                            Department that further inquiry would be neither helpful nor desirable.
                            Take no action.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>